'''Marin Pongračić''' ({{IPA|hr|mâriːn pǒnɡratʃitɕ}};<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hjp.znanje.hr/index.php?show=search_by_id&id=e1xhXBc%3D|title=Mȁrīn|quote=Mȁrīn|website=Hrvatski jezični portal|accessdate=2018-03-17|language=hr}}</ref> born 11 September 1997) is a professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[Defender (association football)|defender]] for {{Italian football updater|Fiorentina}} club [[ACF Fiorentina|Fiorentina]]. Born in Germany, he plays for the [[Croatia national football team|Croatia national team]]. Primarily a [[centre-back]], he can also be deployed as a [[right-back]] or as a [[defensive midfielder]].

==Club career==
===1860 Munich===
Pongračić started his football career as a product of [[FC Bayern Munich|Bayern Munich]] [[FC Bayern Munich Junior Team|academy]], before moving to [[FC Ingolstadt 04]] in 2013 at the age of 16. He made 38 appearances at under-17 and under-19 levels, before moving to [[TSV 1860 Munich|1860 Munich]] in 2016 in search of professional football. After establishing himself in the [[TSV 1860 Munich II|reserve team]], he made his [[2016–17 2. Bundesliga|2. Bundesliga]] debut on 16 April 2017 in a 1–1 draw with [[SV Sandhausen|Sandhausen]]. He made seven appearances for the first team, including an appearance in a [[2016–17 2. Bundesliga#Relegation play-offs|relegation play-off]] against [[SSV Jahn Regensburg|Jahn Regensburg]]. Pongračić was [[Red card (association football)|sent off]] in the 80th minute, as the match ended up as a 1–1 draw.<ref name=":0">{{Cite web|last=|first=|date=2020-01-15|title=Marin Pongracic: Who is Wolfsburg's Croatia U21 international?|url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/bundesliga/news/marin-pongracic-who-is-wolfsburg-s-croatia-u21-international-9294|access-date=2020-08-18|website=Bundesliga|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=|first=|date=2017-04-16|title=TSV 1860 Munich vs. SV Sandhausen - Football Match Report|url=https://www.espn.in/football/report?gameId=456946|access-date=2020-08-18|website=ESPN|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=|first=|date=2017-05-26|title=Neuhaus gibt den Löwen wieder Puls|url=https://www.kicker.de/regensburg-gegen-muenchen-2017-bundesliga-relegation-3812713/spielinfo|access-date=2020-08-18|website=Kicker|language=de-DE}}</ref>

===Red Bull Salzburg===
In summer 2017, he joined Austrian club [[FC Red Bull Salzburg|Red Bull Salzburg]] on a four-year deal.<ref>{{Cite web|last=|first=|date=2017-06-20|title=Salzburg doveo mladog Hrvata koji je karijeru počeo u Bayernu|url=http://www.germanijak.hr/app-germania/vijesti/salzburg-dobeo-mladog-hrvata-koji-je-karijeru-poceo-u-bayernu/32782|access-date=2020-08-18|website=Germanijak}}</ref> He made his debut for the club on 22 July in a 2–0 victory over [[Wolfsberger AC]].<ref>{{Cite web|last=|first=|date=2017-07-22|title=Wolfsberger vs. FC Salzburg - Football Match Summary|url=https://www.espn.com/soccer/match?gameId=484985|access-date=2020-08-18|website=ESPN|language=en}}</ref> However, due to an abductor muscle injury, he missed thirteen games for the club. He returned to the team for the 5 November game against [[SKN St. Pölten|St. Pölten]]. He made his [[2017–18 UEFA Europa League|UEFA Europa League]] debut on 23 November in a 3–0 victory over [[Vitória S.C.|Vitória Guimarães]].<ref>{{Cite web|last=|first=|date=2017-11-23|title=LIVE Red Bull Salzburg - Vitória Guimarães - Europa League|url=https://www.eurosport.com/football/europa-league/2017-2018/live-red-bull-salzburg-vitoria-guimaraes_mtc949242/live.shtml|access-date=2020-08-18|website=Eurosport}}</ref> He then featured throughout Salzburg's Europa League campaign as they reached the [[2017–18 UEFA Europa League knockout phase#Semi-finals|semi-final]], where they were eliminated by [[Olympique de Marseille|Marseille]].<ref>{{Cite web|last=|first=|date=2018-05-03|title=Atletico uništio Arsenalove snove o Ligi prvaka, Marseille preživio Salzburg|url=https://gol.dnevnik.hr/clanak/rubrika/nogomet/europska-liga-atletico-madrid-u-finalu-salzburg-i-marseille-igraju-produzetak---515933.html|access-date=2020-08-18|website=Gol.hr|language=hr}}</ref> Salzburg ended the [[2017–18 FC Red Bull Salzburg season|season]] as the [[2017–18 Austrian Football Bundesliga|Austrian champions]].<ref name=":0" />

On 29 August 2018, in a [[2018–19 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] [[2018–19 UEFA Champions League qualifying phase and play-off round#Play-off round|qualifying play-off]] [[2018–19 UEFA Champions League qualifying phase and play-off round#PO C1.2|return leg]] against [[2018–19 Red Star Belgrade season|Red Star Belgrade]], with Salzburg 2–0 up on the night and seemingly comfortably headed towards Champions League qualification, Pongračić received a 63rd-minute [[Yellow card (association football)|yellow card]] for fouling [[Milan Pavkov]] by stomping on him. The game ended a 2–2 draw and Red Star qualified [[Away goals rule|on away goals]]. Red Star captain [[Vujadin Savić]] later credited Pongračić's foul for providing extra motivation to the Belgrade club, calling Pongračić out for "[[Croatia–Serbia football rivalry|provocations]] throughout the entire match."<ref>{{Cite web|last1=Lovrić|first1=Dejan|last2=Ćubel|first2=Jelena|date=2018-08-30|title=Crvena zvezda u Ligi prvaka: Pongračić je u nama probudio srpski inat!|url=https://www.goal.com/hr-ba/vijesti/crvena-zvezda-salzburg-liga-prvaka-marin-pongracic/a6rlfhyl9plr1bx7pkzhge26q|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180831130301/https://www.goal.com/hr-ba/vijesti/crvena-zvezda-salzburg-liga-prvaka-marin-pongracic/a6rlfhyl9plr1bx7pkzhge26q|archive-date=31 August 2018|url-status=dead|access-date=6 October 2024|website=Goal.com|language=hr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Buškulić|first=Ante|date=2020-08-29|title=Crvena zvezda prvi put u Ligi prvaka, Salzburg najveći luzer!|url=https://www.goal.com/hr/vijesti/liga-prvaka-crvena-zvezda-salzburg/16wlq2cdpybrj1tsmssry7udqz|access-date=2020-08-18|website=Goal.com|language=hr}}</ref> On 21 February 2019, he provided [[Patson Daka]] with an assist for the second goal as Salzburg defeated [[Club Brugge KV|Club Brugge]] 4–0 in [[2018–19 UEFA Europa League|Europa League]] [[2018–19 UEFA Europa League knockout phase#Round of 32|round of 32]].<ref>{{Cite web|last=Hina|date=2019-02-22|title=Dalić može mirno spavati: Perišić i Rebić zabili, stoper Pongračić asistirao za gol|url=https://gol.dnevnik.hr/clanak/rubrika/nogomet/europska-liga-rebic-i-perisic-zabili-u-pobjedama-pongracica-asistirao---550366.html|access-date=2020-08-18|website=Gol.hr|language=hr}}</ref> In his second season at the club, Pongračić helped Salzburg win the [[Double (association football)|double]].<ref name=":0" />

During the first half of the [[2019–20 FC Red Bull Salzburg season|2019–20 season]], he made only seven appearances for the club due to injuries. On 5 November, he made his [[2019–20 UEFA Champions League|Champions League]] debut in a 1–1 draw with [[S.S.C. Napoli|Napoli]].<ref>{{Cite web|last=B. M.|date=2019-11-05|title=Pongračić od prve minute protiv Napolija!|url=https://www.artinfo.ba/index.php/sport/21148-pongracic-od-prve-minute-protiv-napolija|access-date=2020-08-18|website=ARTinfo|language=hr-hr}}</ref>

===VfL Wolfsburg===
After the injury-stricken stint at Salzburg, Pongračić joined [[VfL Wolfsburg]] on 15 January 2020 on a four-and-a-half-year deal for a fee believed to be €10 million.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://onefootball.com/en/news/official-marin-pongracic-joins-wolfsburg-for-10m-28753531?variable=20200117|title=Marin Pongračić joins Wolfsburg for €10m|website=One Football|date=15 January 2020|accessdate=27 May 2020}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=|first=|date=2020-01-15|title=Pongracic leaves for Wolfsburg|url=https://www.redbullsalzburg.at/en/fc-red-bull-salzburg/news/saison_2019_20/pongracic-leaves-for-wolfsburg.html|access-date=2020-08-18|website=FC Red Bull Salzburg|language=en}}</ref> On 8 February, in his second appearance for the club, he was sent off after elbowing [[Alfredo Morales]], as Wolfsburg drew 1–1 with [[Fortuna Düsseldorf]].<ref>{{Cite web|last=Hina|date=2020-02-08|title=Pongračić dobio crveni karton, Brekalo ostao na klupi Vukova|url=https://www.24sata.hr/sport/pongracic-dobio-crveni-karton-brekalo-ostao-na-klupi-vukova-674853|access-date=2020-08-18|website=24sata|language=hr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=D. L.|date=2020-02-11|title=Pongračić dobio crveni karton pa udario po kameri: "Nismo na seoskoj utakmici"|url=https://www.index.hr/clanak.aspx?id=2155734|access-date=2020-08-18|website=Index.hr|language=hr}}</ref> On 26 May, Pongračić scored twice as Wolfsburg defeated [[Bayer Leverkusen]] by a score of 4–1.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.foxsports.com/soccer/video/1742560835694|title=Wolfsburg stuns Leverkusen in 4-1 blowout behind two goals from Marin Pongra|website=FOX Sports|date=26 May 2020|accessdate=27 May 2020}}</ref>

After he missed the beginning of the new [[2020–21 VfL Wolfsburg season|season]] due to [[Infectious mononucleosis|mononucleosis]], Pongračić returned to the team on 8 November as an injury time substitute for [[Xaver Schlager]] in the 2–1 victory over [[TSG 1899 Hoffenheim|1899 Hoffenheim]].<ref>{{Cite web|last1=Dobrinić|first1=Damir|last2=Hina|date=2020-11-08|title=Lovren izborio penal, Juranović zabio autogol, veliki hrvatski talent vratio se na teren nakon 95 dana!|url=https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/sn/nogomet/nogomet-mix/lovren-izborio-penal-juranovic-zabio-autogol-veliki-hrvatski-talent-vratio-se-na-teren-nakon-95-dana-15030288|access-date=|website=Sportske novosti|language=hr-hr}}</ref> However, on 18 November, he tested positive for [[Coronavirus disease 2019|COVID-19]].<ref>{{Cite web|last=|first=|date=2020-11-18|title=Marin Pongračić pozitivan na koronavirus|url=https://hns-cff.hr/news/22036/marin-pongracic-pozitivan-na-koronavirus/|access-date=2020-11-18|website=Hrvatski nogometni savez|language=hr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vfl-wolfsburg.de/newsdetails/news-detail/detail/news/positiver-corona-test-bei-pongracic/|title=Positiver Corona-Test bei Pongracic|date=18 November 2020|access-date=29 May 2021|website=vfl-wolfsburg.de|language=de}}</ref> On 27 February 2021, he was sent off in the injury time of a 2–0 victory over [[Hertha Berlin]].

====Borussia Dortmund (loan)====
On 31 August 2021, Pongračić joined [[Borussia Dortmund]] on loan for the duration of the [[2021–22 Borussia Dortmund season|2021–22 season]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bvb.de/News/Uebersicht/Borussia-Dortmund-verpflichtet-Pongracic|title=Borussia Dortmund verpflichtet Pongracic|website=www.bvb.de|language=German|date=31 August 2021}}</ref> He made his Dortmund debut on 11 September in a 4–3 victory over Bayer Leverkusen.

===Lecce===
On 22 August 2022, Pongračić moved on loan to [[U.S. Lecce|Lecce]] in Italy, with an option to buy.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Lecce|url=http://www.uslecce.it/news/197934878214/marin-pongracic-e-un-nuovo-calciatore-del-lecce|title=MARIN PONGRAČIĆ È UN NUOVO CALCIATORE DEL LECCE|date=22 August 2022|access-date=24 August 2022|language=it}}</ref>

On 30 June 2023, Lecce announced that they had exercised their option to buy with the defender signing an initial two-year deal with the option for a further year.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uslecce.it/news/534821375494/pongracic-in-giallorosso|trans-title=PONGRACIC IN YELLOW AND RED|title=PONGRACIC IN GIALLOROSSO|language=Italian|website=www.uslecce.it|date=30 June 2023|accessdate=30 June 2023|archive-date=29 November 2023|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20231129174252/https://www.uslecce.it/news/534821375494/pongracic-in-giallorosso|url-status=dead}}</ref>

===Fiorentina===
On 19 July 2024, Pongračić joined fellow [[Serie A]] club [[ACF Fiorentina|Fiorentina]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.acffiorentina.com/it/news/tutte/prima-squadra-maschile/2024-07-19/pongracic-e-un-nuovo-calciatore-della-fiorentina|trans-title=IRST TEAM PONGRACIC IS A NEW FIORENTINA PLAYER|title=PONGRACIC È UN NUOVO CALCIATORE DELLA FIORENTINA|language=Italian|website=www.acffiorentina.com|date=19 July 2024|accessdate=19 July 2024}}</ref>

==International career==
Eligible to represent [[Germany national football team|Germany]] and [[Croatia national football team|Croatia]], Pongračić was called up to a training camp for the [[Croatia national under-17 football team|Croatia U17]]s in 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hns-cff.hr/news/4597/kamp-u-17-reprezentacije-u-slavonskom-brodu/|title=Kamp U-17 reprezentacije u Slavonskom Brodu|website=Croatian Football Federation}}</ref> He was capped three times on [[Croatia national under-21 football team|under-21]] level, against [[Moldova national under-21 football team|Moldova]], [[Austria national under-21 football team|Austria]] and [[France national under-21 football team|France]].<ref>{{Cite web|last=|first=|date=|title=Marin Pongračić|url=https://hns-cff.hr/players/428896/marin-pongracic/|access-date=2020-08-18|website=Croatian Football Federation |language=hr}}</ref> He was dropped from [[2019 UEFA European Under-21 Championship squads#Croatia|Croatia's squad]] for [[2019 UEFA European Under-21 Championship|UEFA Under-21 Euro 2019]] due to injuries.<ref name=":1">{{Cite web|last=Škrlec|first=Silvijo|date=2020-05-25|title=Nenad Gračan otkrio nam najveću vrlinu mladog Hrvata koji je zaludio njemačku Bundesligu i nameće se izborniku Daliću: Ima brzinu, ali ima i...|url=https://www.tportal.hr/sport/clanak/nenad-gracan-otkrio-nam-najvecu-vrlinu-mladog-hrvata-koji-je-zaludio-njemacku-bundesligu-i-koji-bi-trebao-postati-dalicev-igrac-20200525|access-date=2020-08-18|website=Tportal.hr|language=hr}}</ref>

He received his first call-up for the senior team on 17 August 2020 for September [[2020–21 UEFA Nations League A#Group 3|Nations League]] fixtures against [[Portugal national football team|Portugal]] and [[France national football team|France]].<ref>{{Cite web|last=Kovačević|first=Davor|date=2020-08-17|title=Dalić pozvao dva debitanta za Ligu nacija: Idemo na Portugal i Francuze s najjačim sastavom|url=https://www.24sata.hr/sport/dalicev-pozvao-dva-debitanta-za-ligu-nacija-idemo-na-portugal-i-francuze-s-najjacim-sastavom-711417|access-date=2020-08-18|website=24sata|language=hr}}</ref> However, ten days later, he withdrew from the squad due to [[Infectious mononucleosis|mononucleosis]] and was replaced by [[Mile Škorić]].<ref>{{Cite web|last=J. B.|date=2020-08-27|title=Modrić i Rakitić propuštaju okupljanje: Dalić pozvao dva igrača iz HNL-a i napadača iz Primere|url=https://gol.dnevnik.hr/clanak/rubrika/nogomet/dalic-aktivirao-pretpoziv-mili-skoricu---618119.html|access-date=|website=Gol.hr|language=hr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=Olivari|first=Davorin|date=2020-08-28|title=Šok iz Njemačke: Umjesto ostvarenja snova, noćna mora – novi Vatreni ima mononukleozu!|url=https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/sn/nogomet/bundesliga/sok-iz-njemacke-umjesto-ostvarenja-snova-nocna-mora-novi-vatreni-ima-mononukleozu-15015906|access-date=|website=Sportske novosti|language=hr-hr}}</ref> He was called up once again on 4 November for same-month fixtures against [[Turkey national football team|Turkey]], [[Sweden men's national football team|Sweden]] and Portugal.<ref>{{Cite web|author-link=Croatian News Agency|author=HINA|date=2020-11-04|title=Dalić aktivirao pet pretpoziva s liste kandidata: Dvojici će to biti prvo okupljanje|url=https://gol.dnevnik.hr/clanak/hrvatska-reprezentacija/dalic-aktivirao-pet-pretpoziva-s-liste-kandidata-dvojici-ce-to-biti-prvo-okupljanje---626760.html|access-date=2020-11-11|website=Gol.hr|language=hr}}</ref> He made his debut on 11 November in a friendly 3–3 draw with Turkey, having been named in the starting lineup.<ref>{{Cite web|last=|first=|date=2020-11-11|title=ANKETA Tko vas je oduševio, a tko razočarao u nikad viđenom sastavu Hrvatske?|url=https://www.index.hr/clanak.aspx?id=2229616|access-date=2020-11-11|website=Index.hr|language=hr}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|last=|first=|date=2020-11-11|title=PONGRAČIĆ: 'Nemam riječi, ispunio mi se san'|url=http://sportklub.hr/Video/Nogomet/Ostala-natjecanja/a130122-PONGRACIC-Nemam-rijeci-ispunio-mi-se-san.html|access-date=2020-11-11|website=Sport Klub|language=hr|archive-date=12 November 2020|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20201112201244/http://sportklub.hr/Video/Nogomet/Ostala-natjecanja/a130122-PONGRACIC-Nemam-rijeci-ispunio-mi-se-san.html|url-status=dead}}</ref>

On 17 May 2021, Pongračić was named in the preliminary 34-man squad for the [[UEFA Euro 2020]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://gol.dnevnik.hr/clanak/rubrika/nogomet/popis-hrvatske-za-euro-2020-ovo-je-26-vatrenih-koji-putuju-na-europsko-prvenstvo---652063.html |title=Dalić objavio popis za Euro 2020: Poznato svih 26 imena, izbornik objasnio iznenađenje |website=Gol.hr |date=2021-05-17 |access-date=2022-12-21 |language=hr}}</ref> but did not make the [[UEFA Euro 2020 squads#Croatia|final 26]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://gol.dnevnik.hr/clanak/hrvatska-reprezentacija/zlatko-dalic-potvrdio-popis-26-igraca-za-europsko-prvenstvo-2020---654181.html |title=Sada je konačno: Dalić potvrdio popis od 26 igrača za Euro 2020 |website=Gol.hr |date=2021-06-01 |access-date=2022-12-21 |language=hr |author=HINA |author-link=Croatian News Agency}}</ref>

On 31 October 2022, he was named in the preliminary 34-man squad for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]],<ref>{{cite web |url=https://gol.dnevnik.hr/clanak/rubrika/sp-2022/prosireni-popis-zlatka-dalica-za-svjetsko-prvenstvo---749474.html |title=Dalić objavio prošireni popis za Svjetsko prvenstvo: Evo tko ima šansu putovati u Katar |website=Gol.hr |date=2022-10-31 |access-date=2022-12-21 |language=hr}}</ref> but did not make the [[2022 FIFA World Cup squads#Croatia|final 26]] again.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.vecernji.hr/sport/uzivo-od-11-sati-zlatko-dalic-objavljuje-konacni-popis-igraca-za-sp-1632085 |title=Zlatko Dalić objavio popis igrača za SP, ovo su 26 imena koje vodi u Katar |website=Večernji list |date=2022-11-09 |access-date=2022-12-21 |language=hr}}</ref>

== Personal life ==
Pongračić was born in [[Landshut]], Germany. His parents Stribor and Anđelka fled from [[Slavonski Brod]], Croatia to Germany during the [[Croatian War of Independence]].<ref name=":1" /><ref name=":2">{{Cite web|last=Antolić|first=Dražen|date=2020-05-21|title='Modrić i Rakitić nikad nisu čuli za mene!' Najbrži stoper priznao: Dalić mi je rekao da me prati!|url=https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/sn/nogomet/bundesliga/modric-i-rakitic-nikad-nisu-culi-za-mene-najbrzi-stoper-priznao-dalic-mi-je-rekao-da-me-prati-15001018|access-date=2020-08-18|website=Sportske novosti|language=hr-hr}}</ref>

Pongračić named [[Kalidou Koulibaly]] and [[Virgil van Dijk]] his football idols.<ref name=":2"/> He is also a fan of [[GNK Dinamo Zagreb|Dinamo Zagreb]].<ref>{{Cite web |last=Antolić |first=Dražen |date=2022-03-28 |title=Igrač Borussije i navijač Dinama koji je iskoristio svoju priliku: 'Hrvatska ima veliki potencijal' |url=https://sportske.jutarnji.hr/sn/nogomet/reprezentacija/igrac-borussije-i-navijac-dinama-koji-je-iskoristio-svoju-priliku-hrvatska-ima-veliki-potencijal-15176271 |access-date=2022-03-28 |website=Sportske novosti |language=hr-hr}}</ref>

==Career statistics==
